    // EXPANDED TOUR SECTIONS IN ENGLISH
    'tour_free_title': 'üö∂‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è Free Tour - Discover Imperial Toledo',
    'tour_free_description':
        'Embark on a fascinating journey through 2000 years of Toledo\'s history with our specialized free tour. Explore the most emblematic points of the Imperial City: from the imposing Primate Cathedral to the mysterious alleys of the Jewish quarter, passing through the majestic Alc√°zar, ancient mosques converted into churches, and viewpoints offering spectacular views of the Tagus meander. Our expert guides will reveal hidden secrets, urban legends, and historical curiosities you won\'t find in conventional tourist guides. Discover why Toledo was called the "City of Three Cultures," learn anecdotes about El Greco and his era, and understand how medieval tolerance created a unique artistic heritage in the world. Duration: 2.5 hours. Meeting point: Plaza de Zocodover. Schedule: 10:30, 16:00, and 18:30 (summer schedule). Includes access to exclusive interior courtyards and artisanal marzipan tasting.',

    'tour_cultural_title': 'üèõÔ∏è Cultural Tourism - Imperial Heritage',
    'tour_cultural_description':
        'Immerse yourself in an exceptional cultural journey through Toledo, the city that treasures Spain\'s greatest monumental heritage. Visit the Primate Cathedral, a masterpiece of Spanish Gothic that houses the famous Baroque Transparente and one of Europe\'s richest sacristies with works by El Greco, Goya, and Caravaggio. Explore the Imperial Alc√°zar, witness to historical battles and current seat of the Army Museum with unique collections of medieval armor, historical weapons, and Spain\'s most important military history library. Discover the Mud√©jar synagogues of Santa Mar√≠a la Blanca and El Tr√°nsito, unique in Europe for their architecture and decoration, housing the Sephardic Museum with original Hebrew manuscripts. Tour the mosques of Cristo de la Luz (10th century) and Las Torner√≠as, exceptional testimonies of Hispano-Muslim art with original Kufic inscriptions. Visit the El Greco Museum to contemplate masterpieces by the Cretan painter in the historical environment that inspired them, including "View and Plan of Toledo" and "The Disrobing of Christ." Includes priority access to monuments, specialized audio guides, and visits to Mud√©jar churches like Santiago del Arrabal and San Rom√°n with their spectacular coffered ceilings.',

    'tour_gastronomy_title': 'üç∑ Gastronomy - Flavors of History',
    'tour_gastronomy_description':
        'Embark on a unique culinary experience that combines traditional flavors with Toledo\'s millenary history. Discover authentic Toledan marzipan, crafted since the 11th century in convent workshops with secret recipes transmitted by generations of Clarist nuns using only regional Marcona almonds and sugar. Taste the famous Toledan carcamusas in centennial taverns of the Jewish quarter, where each tavern master jealously guards their family recipe combining Iberian pork, tomato, peas, and spices in slow cooking. Try the "Toledan-style" stewed partridge with chocolate, a unique dish combining hunting tradition with 17th-century conventual influences. Savor artisanal cheeses from Los Montes de Toledo made with milk from native goats grazing in Mediterranean dehesas. Professional wine pairings with Denomination of Origin "Montes de Toledo" wines in historical cellars excavated in volcanic rock. Includes visits to traditional workshops on Comercio Street, tastings led by sommeliers specialized in Castilian gastronomy, conventional sweet-making workshops, and themed dinners in restaurants located in Renaissance palaces and noble houses of the historic center with live traditional music.',

    'tour_nature_title': 'üåø Nature - Tagus Ecosystems',
    'tour_nature_description':
        'Discover the natural treasures that surround Toledo in a Mediterranean landscape of extraordinary beauty and internationally recognized ecological richness. Explore the Natural Park of Montes de Toledo, declared a Protected Natural Space by the Junta de Castilla-La Mancha, where millenary oak dehesas house protected native fauna including the Iberian lynx (endangered species), imperial eagles, griffon vultures, black storks, and Palearctic otters. Walk interpretive signposted trails that cross native forests of centennial oaks, cork oaks, and Portuguese oaks where endemic wild orchids like Orchis champagneuxii bloom in spring. Navigate ecological boats on the Tagus River discovering unique riparian ecosystems with gallery vegetation including centennial white poplars, weeping willows, ash trees, and elms where more than 150 species of migratory birds nest. Observe from conditioned natural viewpoints the spectacular views of the Toledan meander embracing the historic city, formed by millions of years of fluvial erosion. Includes specialized ornithological routes to spot protected species, nature photography workshops with professional equipment, botanical excursions led by certified naturalist guides, and sustainable active tourism activities like interpretive hiking, ecological cycling on green routes, and supervised climbing on the Tagus limestone cliffs.',

    'tour_nightlife_title': 'üåô Nocturnal Toledo - Magic and Mystery',
    'tour_nightlife_description':
        'Experience the nocturnal magic of Toledo when the golden lights of artistic illumination transform the city into a dreamlike scenario charged with mystery and romance worthy of B√©cquer\'s legends. Participate in themed nocturnal tours "Magical Toledo" that reveal historically documented urban legends, registered apparitions in municipal archives, and hidden secrets of the imperial city narrated by guides specialized in Toledan folklore. Walk medieval cobblestone alleys illuminated by wrought iron lanterns projecting mysterious shadows on Renaissance palaces, Mud√©jar houses, and cloistered convents where Gregorian chants still resound. Enjoy authentic flamenco performances in natural caves and historic courtyards where professional guitarists and singers interpret traditional pieces while musical notes reverberate among centennial walls charged with history. Taste artisanal cocktails inspired by medieval recipes in themed bars located in restored historic buildings preserving original Gothic vaults, polychrome Mud√©jar arches, and Renaissance courtyards with marble fountains. Contemplate exclusive nocturnal panoramic views from private elevated terraces and secret viewpoints offering unique perspectives of the illuminated city reflecting in the Tagus waters. Includes intimate classical music and contemporary jazz concerts in historic churches with exceptional acoustics, medieval themed dinners with theatrical historical performances, exclusive access to specially illuminated monuments, and traditional liquor tastings in centennial taverns of the Jewish quarter.',
  },
};

extension LocalizationExtension on BuildContext {
  String tr(String key) {
    final locale = Localizations.localeOf(this).languageCode;
    return translations[locale]?[key] ?? translations['es']![key] ?? key;
  }
}

// Funci√≥n global para compatibilidad hacia atr√°s
String tr(BuildContext context, String key) {
